# Estate Light Flicker™

**Canonical CSS:** `app/companion/estate-light-flicker.css`

Any visible **lantern**, **candle**, or **fireplace** in the Estate should feel alive — soft warm flicker, never strobe or arcade flash.

## When you add warm light

1. Place a **blurred radial-gradient overlay** aligned to the flame in the image (not a cartoon flame sprite).
2. Apply one of:
   - `className="estate-light-glow estate-light-glow--lantern"` (or `--candle` / `--fireplace`)
   - `data-estate-light="lantern"` (or `candle` / `fireplace`) on the overlay element
3. Stagger siblings with `estate-light-glow--delay-1` … `--delay-4` or `data-estate-light-delay="1"` … `"4"`.
4. Set `aria-hidden="true"` and `pointer-events: none` on decorative overlays.

## Animation map

| Light | Keyframe | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------|
| Lantern (scene overlay) | `estate-lantern-flicker` | 2.6s linear |
| Lamppost glass glow | `estate-lamppost-lantern-flicker` | opacity only — keeps `translateX(-50%)` |
| Candle | `estate-candle-flicker` | 2.4s ease-in-out |
| Fireplace | `estate-fireplace-flicker` | 3.8s — **gentle**; half-strength swing |

## Never

- Static glow on a lit lantern/candle in a photo scene
- Harsh pulse (`scale` > 1.05) or fast strobe (< 1.5s on fireplaces)
- Flicker when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` — animations must disable

## Existing patterns (may alias to canonical keyframes)

Peaceful Places · Evening Hearth · Homestead signpost · Clear My Mind fireplace · Focus plaques · hanging destination menus.

When touching those files, prefer `estate-light-flicker.css` utilities over new one-off keyframes.

Aligns with [Spec 103](../docs/UNIVERSAL_EXPERIENCE_STANDARDS_FRAMEWORK.md) visual standards — subtle motion, premium estate feel.
